name: Come On In - The Palominos
description:
Seven original songs by this San Diego California based honky-tonk band plays classic west coast style country with vocal harmonies, steady back-beat and a persistently twanging lead guitar. Not contemporary in style, but certainly timeless in sound. Steeped in the classic honky-tonk of yesteryear, The Palominos bring to the stage and era that's long gone but far from forgotten.

Formed in 2006 by brothers Thomas and James Zurek (on guitar and bass) and playing a mix of both obscure country classics and their own originals, The Palominos present their timeless, toe tapping sound to a modern-day crowd that is sure to bring ...'em out onto the dance floor everywhere they play. 

www.thepalominos.com

Available on iTunes
www.bit.ly/iTunesComeOnIn

name: Heart - Nancarrow
description:
Six new songs by the alt-country band Nancarrow. If Nancarrow’s music seems familiar to you, it’s easy to see why. With members drawing from experience with bands and artists such as Steve Earle, Rhett Miller, Murry Hammond, The White Buffalo, Nipsy Russel, Comanche Moon, and the Dukes of Haggard, their roots run deep in Country and Alternative music. Fronted by 25 year old singer/songwriter Graham Nancarrow, the band infuses raw energy and classic tones to create their own unique brand of pure American music.

www.nancarrowmusic.com

Available on iTunes
www.bit.ly/iTunesHeart

name: New Old Story - Bastard Sons of Johnny Cash
description:
The latest full length CD from the Bastard Sons of Johnny Cash offers up ten new tracks from the band Rolling Stone described as "pure Americana heart and soul".

The Bastard Sons of Johnny Cash are the voice and vision of songwriter Mark Stuart. Since forming the group in 1995, he's shared the stage with such notables as Merle Haggard, Buck Owens, Willie Nelson, George Jones, Lucinda Williams, and Steve Earle. He's built an international reputation as a skilled recording artist, producer, and tireless live performer. He was personally given permission to use the band's name by the "Man in Black" himself - and Stuart and the band also received the additional endorsement of an invitation to record at Cash's home studio "The Cash Cabin" in Hendersonville, TN.

www.bsojc.com

Available on iTunes
www.bit.ly/iTunesNewOldStory

name: Wolf Prize - Tori
description:
The latest EP from Tori Rogg, "Wolf Prize' offers up six new tracks from this special singer/songwriter.  

After playing locally for a short period of time Tori was asked to share the stage with some well-known artists, such as: Colbie Collait, Jewel, Melissa Ferrick, Sia, KD Lang, Iron and Wine, John Waite, James and more. This wonderfully talented artist-on-the-rise brings unprecedented musicality to all of her songs. By piecing together heart-felt words inspired by real-life experiences, Tori’s edgy  but “down-to-earth” style make listeners feel like each song was written specifically for them.

name: Oh Dry Land - John Meeks
description:
The latest EP from John Meeks offers up five new tracks from this long established singer/songwriter from San Diego.

John Meeks spent the earlier part of his life roaming the southwest with his freewheelin' mother and two younger siblings in an often broken down Chrysler New Yorker. He eventually settled in San Diego, with summers spent wandering through the honky tonks of New Mexico where his talented and charismatic father played drums and sang in a working country band.

www.johnmeeks.com

name: Home (Remix) - Pi Jacobs
description:
Our first 12" vinyl single is a special one - Side A features our first ever remix, a killer version of "Home" by Pi Jacobs, remixed by Eugene Toale.  Side B follows that up with the original mix, an instrumental and an accapella - a little something for everyone! 

Pi Jacobs is a singer-songwriter you've probably heard, even if you haven't heard of her - along with putting in serious road miles, touring the US and the UK, her music has been featured in over 60 placements in television, film, and commercials

Now living in Los Angeles, the native San Franciscan has has worked with several top producers, including Pfilbryte (TommyBoy - Ignition), and Randy Wine (U2, Aretha Franklin).

Pi’s forthcoming fifth album, UrbaniCana, was collaboration with renowned producer Eugene Toale, whose credits include Kanye West, Mya, Brandy, and Raekwon, and features The Beastie Boy’s drummer, Fredo Ortiz, on every track.

www.pijacobs.com

name: Photos of Madrid - Filligar
description:
A new 7" 45 vinyl from Filligar, featuring their single "Photos of Madrid" and a remixed version by Kent Rockafeller.

Filligar is a touring indie rock quartet hailed as "one of the best young bands in America." The lineup -- three Mathias brothers and Casey Gibson -- remains unchanged since the band's early days recording and performing as teenagers in Chicago. Live performance is the band's lifeblood. They've been named one of music's "Next Big Things" by SPIN Magazine and listed along with Wilco, Delta Spirit, and Heartless Bastards "One of America's Top 8 Live Acts" (Boston's RSLmusic blog).

www.filligar.com

name: I'm Going Home - My Goodness
description:
7" 45 vinyl from the Seattle based band, My Goodness featuring their new single, "In The Sun" b/w a ripping cover of The Sonics's classic, "I'm Going Home.

My Goodness is a Seattle-based blues/garage rock band that consists of Joel Schneider (Guitar/Vocals) and Andy Lum (Drums). After releasing their self-titled album in 2011, My Goodness was on hold for the majority of 2012, but with the recent addition of Andy Lum it has found a renewed purpose, moving forward with a heavier, more aggressive sound. Straddling the line between raw and refined, My Goodness doesn’t sacrifice technical precision in the name of punk rock - they strive to marry both.

www.mygoodnessmusic.com
